[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Welcome back to the channel where Bob Doyle discusses the creative uses of AI. And with more and more all-in-one tool platforms out there, it\'s important that they bring something unique to the table, like their own models, which rival the quality of the better known'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'players. &gt;&gt; Today\'s sponsor, Po.ai, is one such platform that has brought its own models to the table. Both a video model, which you saw at the beginning of this. That\'s right. It was not Veo. It was not Sora. It was not any other video model that includes sound effects and video, but'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the Po 2 video model, which includes both of those and is super fast and extremely accurate. I\'m going to show you exactly how accurate in just a couple of minutes. But before I do, let me just first introduce you to the Po platform if you have not seen it before.'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It is another all-in-one platform, but as I say, it brings its own presence to the party. But that\'s not to say it doesn\'t play well with others. you\'ll find with a little investigation that they have all the top models for both video and image production, including of course Nano Banana Pro, which just hit'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the scene a couple of days ago. So, let\'s start with that because right now they\'ve got a 50% offer going there. And if you haven\'t played with it yet, this would be a good place to start. Like some other platforms, you have the ability to organize your work into projects. You can keep everything related in the same place. And you can'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'also easily see all of your creations all in one place by clicking my creations. And they have them nicely categorized. You can see everything you\'ve done. You can just see your videos, any of their fun AI video effects, which we\'re going to take a'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'look at. And of course, any images you create. When you create a new project, you have two choices, easy mode or canvas mode. For the purposes of right now, we\'re just going to go ahead and go into easy mode and create a new project up here and just click on text to image. It\'s going to bring us to this interface'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here where we have a drop-own list where we can choose from any of the image models. Now, you\'ll see that it even has things like midjourney, seedream, the flux models, Quinn, Juan, just all of them. So, we would just choose Nano Banana Pro. We have the ability to'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'choose a wide range of aspect ratios and the number of images we want output as well as resolutions all the way up to 4K. Just really quick, let\'s do a quick comparison between the standard Nano Banana model and what the new Pro model is able to do. This is an example of the'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'standard NanoBanana model with the prompt golden hour portrait in a field of tall grass, warm rim light behind the subject, 50mm lens, soft bokeh, gentle wind, natural skin tones, realistic atmospheric haze. We have four different'

