AUDIO: 'these were all also created with the PO 1.6 model. Along the left, the creation tools are actually divided into two sections here. We have image where we have access to our text to image, image to image, and chat to image when we\'re in this canvas mode here, which allows'

[04:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'us to make changes to any image just by giving it a text prompt here. This canvas mode, by the way, which is their more advanced mode, gives you access to a different level of ability to organize and move these around and to compare. You\'re also just one click away from'

[04:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tools like impainting and upscaling your image and unccropping which allows you to extend the image beyond its current borders. You can erase objects from any image. You can remove the background or you can change it completely with a prompt and even basic functionality like'

[05:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cropping. Now I\'m excited to show you the PO2 video model because it really does an excellent job even compared to the ones you\'re more familiar with. To use it, we just go over to AI video. We\'ll click on text to video first. With the PO2 model like Veo and Sora, you can'

[05:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt in sound effects. You can prompt in what you want it to say. You can start with the starting image or you can start with text. So, let\'s start with text first so we can show you how that looks. You of course have various aspect ratio choices you can make. How many'

[05:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'videos up to four you want to output. The resolution goes all the way up to 1080p and you get a generation of not 8 seconds, but 10 seconds if you want it. This was my first test with the Po 2 model, and I got bold and brave to see'

